1	//! The `finalize` subcommand: squash + set-bookmark + push a jj
2	//! repo, optionally detached so trailing writes land first.
3	//!
4	//! Built for the bot to atomically finalize its `.claude` session
5	//! repo at end-of-step. Every action is opt-in (`--squash`,
6	//! `--push`, `--detach`, `--delay`). The detached path re-execs
7	//! `vc-x1 finalize --exec …` so its output and errors survive the
8	//! parent exiting; failures are dropped as markers under
9	//! `~/.cache/vc-x1/finalize-status` and surfaced on the next
10	//! `vc-x1` run.
11	
12	use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};
13	use std::process::Stdio;
14	use std::time::{SystemTime, UNIX_EPOCH};
15	
16	use clap::Args;
17	use log::{debug, info};
